Barcelona boss, Ronald Koeman in a private chat with Argentine star Lionel Messi dished out his expectations on the players. READ ALSO: Breaking: Messi returns to Barcelona training ground The Dutchman told Messi that he was over the moon he was staying and he did not want to give special treatment to players as he looks to break the player-power mould at Barcelona. According to Mundo Deportivo he also warned him he was only interested in players that were fully committed to Barcelona. Recall that Daily Times reported that Messi opted to leave La Liga giants Barcelona after a shameful 8-2 Bayern Munich defeat. Meanwhile Lionel Messi has  pushed himself in training as he wanted to lead by example, after replyingKoeman he was only interested in bringing back the good times at the Nou Camp.